review_blob: Perfect amber coloring with slight white lacing. Taste of smooth nuts and brown sugar. Could never guess its 8%. Great pub beer!

Allagash White is a very simple beer definitely meant to session. Pale yellow and cloudy in color with a sweet and spicy aroma. Tasty banana and warm spices make a smooth taste for this unfiltered Belgian.
If it wasnt in front of me I wouldnt believe it. Perfect tan head and jet black color. Rich malty smoke flavors with strong fruit finish. Be careful though, this brews got muscle.

review_blob: Sugar, spice, and everything fall. Subtle white head with a pale amber color. Just enough pumpkin and brown sugar to feel warm. Great Autumn brew.
